He takes this job from the Pope.
Good money, good work.

244
00:15:47,740 --> 00:15:49,908
Okay, Father, but why'd
the Pope call him?

245
00:15:50,075 --> 00:15:52,242
Because the Pope was looking for
the best guy he could find...

246
00:15:52,408 --> 00:15:53,867
...to paint the ceiling
of his church in Rome.

247
00:15:54,075 --> 00:15:55,743
It don't sound like
that big a job, Father.

248
00:15:56,035 --> 00:15:57,369
Well, for Michelangelo it was.

249
00:15:57,827 --> 00:15:59,619
Michelangelo needed the job...

250
00:15:59,786 --> 00:16:01,746
...because it paid more money
than he ever had in his life.

251
00:16:02,453 --> 00:16:05,205
And that way, he could pay off the loan
sharks that were chasing his father down.

252
00:16:05,329 --> 00:16:05,997
What's his father?

253
00:16:06,788 --> 00:16:09,832
He was like a low-level...con guy.

254
00:16:09,999 --> 00:16:11,541
Conned people out of money,
goats, sheep...

255
00:16:11,625 --> 00:16:12,374
Goats?

256
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:13,875
Chickens, whatever he could, you know.

257
00:16:14,041 --> 00:16:14,710
-Chickens?
-Chickens?

258
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:16,085
You know what happened?

259
00:16:17,626 --> 00:16:19,378
He painted a ceiling no
one will ever forget.

260
00:16:19,627 --> 00:16:21,419
Painted it like he was touched
by the hand of God.

261
00:16:22,295 --> 00:16:23,503
Did he pay off the loans?

262
00:16:23,671 --> 00:16:24,795
Every single one of them.

263
00:16:25,964 --> 00:16:27,881
How long did it take him,
painting the ceiling and all?

264
00:16:28,048 --> 00:16:29,547
It took him about 9 years.

265
00:16:29,923 --> 00:16:30,965
9 years?!

266
