Hey, just give us a job painting,
and leave the rest to us.

271
00:16:42,970 --> 00:16:44,095
You know what it was?
The Sistine Chapel!

272
00:16:44,428 --> 00:16:46,138
Sixteenth Chapel?

273
00:16:46,305 --> 00:16:47,098
Who painted the other fifteen?

274
00:16:55,725 --> 00:17:00,059
Outside events meant little. In a society
changing radically by the hour...

275
00:17:00,226 --> 00:17:02,977
...we watched the images scatter
nightly across the T.V. screens.

276
00:17:03,436 --> 00:17:06,562
Young protesters spoke about how they
were going to change our lives...

277
00:17:06,646 --> 00:17:10,314
...and fix the world. But while
they shouted their slogans...

278
00:17:11,398 --> 00:17:12,855
...my friends and I went to
funeral services...

279
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:14,481
...for the young men
of Hell's Kitchen...

280
00:17:14,816 --> 00:17:16,942
...who came back from Vietnam
in body bags.

281
00:17:18,276 --> 00:17:20,735
We viewed with skepticism
the faces on television...

282
00:17:21,859 --> 00:17:24,278
...those protected by money and
upper-middle-class standing.

283
00:17:27,655 --> 00:17:30,572
A growing army of feminists
marched across the country...

284
00:17:31,281 --> 00:17:34,490
...demanding equality.
Yet, our mothers still cooked...

285
00:17:34,657 --> 00:17:37,324
...and cared for men who abused
them mentally and physically.

286
00:17:39,450 --> 00:17:42,286
For me and my friends, these
developments carried no weight.

287
00:17:43,202 --> 00:17:46,662
They might as well have occurred in
another country...in another century.

288
00:17:47,954 --> 00:17:49,413
Our attention was elsewhere.

289
00:17:50,205 --> 00:17:53,456
We sat with Father Bobby in a third
floor hospital ward, visiting John...

290
00:17:53,622 --> 00:17:55,123
