You have to keep yourself mean
and cut your life around it!

354
00:20:52,276 --> 00:20:54,319
All right, all right, calm down.

355
00:20:54,402 --> 00:20:56,486
It's like hanging out with fucking
Confucius over here.

356
00:20:56,737 --> 00:20:58,070
Be funny, limp dick.

357
00:20:58,570 --> 00:21:00,403
Look, this is just free advice
from me to you.

358
00:21:00,445 --> 00:21:02,238
You take it or you throw it away.
It don't matter.

359
00:21:02,905 --> 00:21:04,240
Thanks a lot, fat man.

360
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:08,741
In truth, we were all surprised
by Michael's actions.

361
00:21:09,242 --> 00:21:10,826
But in his mind,
losing that game meant...

362
00:21:10,909 --> 00:21:13,325
...handing a feeling of victory
to a girl in a wheelchair...

363
00:21:13,743 --> 00:21:15,327
...was more than the right thing to do.

364
00:21:24,996 --> 00:21:26,456
Come on, let's go swimming.

365
00:21:26,873 --> 00:21:28,874
The temperature topped out
at 98 degrees...

366
00:21:28,957 --> 00:21:31,167
...on the day our lives
were forever altered.

367
00:21:31,583 --> 00:21:34,293
I'm frying like an egg up here.
I say, we get some buttered rolls,

368
00:21:34,459 --> 00:21:36,669
a couple of cold sodas, and head
down to the docks.

369
00:21:36,836 --> 00:21:38,836
Can't you feel the breeze up here?

370
00:21:39,002 --> 00:21:40,920
What breeze?
We're surrounded by a wall, genius!

371
00:21:41,087 --> 00:21:42,003
The devil couldn't stand this heat.

372
00:21:42,087 --> 00:21:43,379
Will you guys shut up, please?

373
00:21:43,504 --> 00:21:44,671
I'm trying to get my burn.

374
00:21:44,838 --> 00:21:46,171
It's 98 degrees!

375
00:21:46,630 --> 00:21:48,923
-There's some breeze up here.
-It's a hot breeze.

376
00:21:49,007 --> 00:21:51,258
We haven't hit the hot dog
vendor in a couple of weeks.

377
00:21:51,924 --> 00:21:54,634
I don't know, Mikey. That cart guy
ain't like the others.

378
00:21:55,009 --> 00:21:58,677
I mean, he gets pretty pissed, like
crazy when you try to take him off.

379
00:21:58,844 --> 00:22:02,387
We can eat hot dogs...
or we can eat air...choose.

380
00:22:04,388 --> 00:22:06,055
Air is probably safer, Mike.

381
00:22:06,305 --> 00:22:08,515
Yeah, a hot dog ain't worth
bleeding over, Mikey.

382
00:22:08,889 --> 00:22:10,723
Yeah, anyway, whose turn is it?

383
00:22:11,224 --> 00:22:12,141
Yours!

384
00:22:12,641 --> 00:22:15,309
-Yeah, it's yours.
-Mine? It's not my turn.

385
00:22:15,559 --> 00:22:17,144
-Yes, it is!
-I went like last month.

386
00:22:17,309 --> 00:22:18,309
-He went two weeks.
-You never went.

387
00:22:18,477 --> 00:22:20,477
-Last month.
-Are you nuts? I went right after him.

388
00:22:20,644 --> 00:22:21,310
I'm not going.

389
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:22,477
-Why?
-It's too hot.

390
00:22:22,853 --> 00:22:24,562
If I walk down the
stairs, I'll pass out.

391
00:22:28,314 --> 00:22:30,023
Mustard and onions. No soda.

392
00:22:30,566 --> 00:22:31,648
I know you!

393
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:33,483
I look like a lot of people.

394
00:22:34,524 --> 00:22:35,650
The scam was simple.

395
00:22:36,233 --> 00:22:39,235
I was to walk up to the hot dog
vendor and order what I wanted.

396
00:22:39,776 --> 00:22:43,069
The vendor would then hand me my hot
dog and watch as I ran off without paying.

397
00:22:43,653 --> 00:22:46,405
This left the vendor with two
choices, neither very appealing.

398
00:22:46,947 --> 00:22:50,031
He could stand his ground and swallow
his loss, or he could give chase.

399
00:22:50,697 --> 00:22:52,364
The second forces him
to abandon the cart...

400
00:22:52,532 --> 00:22:54,449
...where my friends could
feast in his absence.

401
00:22:57,742 --> 00:22:59,325
I'm gonna need two napkins?

402
00:23:01,286 --> 00:23:02,619
Pay my money, thief!

403
00:23:10,247 --> 00:23:11,206
Wow! Ketchup!

404
00:23:11,289 --> 00:23:12,622
I took it from him and ran!

405
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:16,875
I scooted past Tommy Mug's Dry
Cleaners and Armond's Shoe Repair.

406
00:23:17,624 --> 00:23:21,544
The vendor gave chase, a wooden-
handled, pronged fork in one hand.

407
00:23:23,294 --> 00:23:24,129
You gonna give me two?

408
00:23:34,923 --> 00:23:36,591
You know, these things are
heavier than they look.

409
00:23:36,798 --> 00:23:39,759
Genius, it's the gas tanks
to keep the food hot.

410
00:23:39,968 --> 00:23:41,260
They're heavier than shit!

411
00:23:42,051 --> 00:23:43,594
Think we can push it, the three of us?

412
00:23:44,552 --> 00:23:45,636
Push it where?

413
00:23:46,219 --> 00:23:48,886
A couple of blocks. It'll be
a nice surprise for the guy...

414
00:23:49,220 --> 00:23:51,721
...when he comes back from chasing
Shakes, not to find his cart.

415
00:24:13,063 --> 00:24:14,938
The vendor tired at 47th and 9th.

416
00:24:15,398 --> 00:24:16,939
I was on the other side of the street.

417
00:24:19,025 --> 00:24:21,026
He was beat...but not beaten.

418
00:24:21,858 --> 00:24:24,109
He could go ten minutes
more, just on hate alone.

419
00:24:24,610 --> 00:24:27,861
Give it up.

420
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,034
What's wrong, Mikey?

421
00:24:43,201 --> 00:24:46,160
Shakes is taking too long.
He should've been back by now.

422
00:24:47,035 --> 00:24:48,827
He'll be fine. He's Shakes.

423
00:24:51,870 --> 00:24:53,996
You guys were supposed to take
the hot dogs, not the wagon.

424
00:24:54,704 --> 00:24:56,538
-Now he tells us.
-He's coming fast, Mikey.

425
00:24:56,706 --> 00:24:57,665
He still near?

426
00:24:58,374 --> 00:25:00,208
I got a plan! Come on
over by the subway!

427
00:25:01,291 --> 00:25:04,793
The plan was as simple and as dumb
as anything we had ever done.

428
00:25:05,708 --> 00:25:07,876
We were to hold the cart on the top
edge of the stairwell,

429
00:25:07,959 --> 00:25:10,210
Leaning it downward,
and wait for the vendor.

430
00:25:10,419 --> 00:25:12,337
We were to let it go the second
he grabbed the handles.

431
00:25:12,503 --> 00:25:15,672
Then we'd leave the scene as he struggled
to ease the cart back onto the sidewalk.

432
00:25:16,255 --> 00:25:18,422
To this day, I don't
know why we did it.

433
00:25:18,881 --> 00:25:20,340
But, we would all pay a price.

434
00:25:21,132 --> 00:25:25,050
It only took a minute...but
in that minute...everything changed.

435
00:25:26,342 --> 00:25:27,301
Guys, I can't hold it!

436
00:25:27,468 --> 00:25:29,176
-Don't let go!
-I can't hold it!

437
00:25:31,510 --> 00:25:32,220
I can't hold it!

438
00:25:45,891 --> 00:25:47,849
Stop! God, no! !

439
00:26:10,609 --> 00:26:11,443
Damn!

440
00:26:16,945 --> 00:26:20,822
Sweet Jesus! What have you boys done?

441
00:26:21,155 --> 00:26:23,907
What in the name of God
have you boys done?

442
00:26:23,991 --> 00:26:25,324
I think we just killed a man.

443
00:26:30,868 --> 00:26:33,954
While James Caldwell was slowly
recovering at St. Clare's Hospital...

444
00:26:34,744 --> 00:26:38,537
