00:49:40,497 --> 00:49:43,038
Well, you love the book that much.
You should have a copy of your own.

722
00:49:43,664 --> 00:49:46,125
-I can't pay you.
-It's a gift.

723
00:49:47,291 --> 00:49:48,624
You've gotten gifts before,
haven't you?

724
00:49:48,792 --> 00:49:49,875
It's been a while.

725
00:49:51,084 --> 00:49:54,419
-Well, it's my way of saying, thanks.
-For what?

726
00:49:55,586 --> 00:49:58,254
That somebody listens...
even if it's just one student.

727
00:49:59,130 --> 00:50:00,505
You're a good teacher, Mr. Carlson.

728
00:50:00,588 --> 00:50:02,796
Listen, we can discuss the book
on Friday in class if you...

729
00:50:03,213 --> 00:50:04,716
...think the Count can
hold their attention.

730
00:50:05,050 --> 00:50:06,215
He's got a shot.

731
00:50:07,049 --> 00:50:08,341
Any particular section
I should read from?

732
00:50:09,092 --> 00:50:11,759
That's easy...the part where
he escapes from prison.

733
00:50:25,432 --> 00:50:28,266
There you go, All Star.
Here's your locker room!

734
00:50:35,810 --> 00:50:40,312
It was only a game...just a touch
football game, nothing more.

735
00:50:41,146 --> 00:50:42,897
But a game I wish we
had never played.

736
00:50:43,939 --> 00:50:47,773
Guards against inmates.
The guards practiced four times a week.

737
00:50:48,607 --> 00:50:50,775
Our team was picked the
Monday before the game.

738
00:50:51,484 --> 00:50:52,983
We had a 2 hour practice.

739
00:50:53,901 --> 00:50:55,109
It didn't matter much.

740
00:50:55,484 --> 00:50:58,485
We weren't supposed to win.
We were just supposed to show up.

741
00:50:59,152 --> 00:51:00,613
Who's the toughest guy here?

742
00:51:01,613 --> 00:51:02,821
How do you mean, tough?

743
00:51:03,321 --> 00:51:04,988
Who can talk and have
everyone listening?

744
00:51:05,156 --> 00:51:07,156
Rizzo. Black kid over there.

745
00:51:09,115 --> 00:51:12,616
Michael saw an opening...a chance
to bring the game to our level.

746
00:51:12,783 --> 00:51:16,785
Even out the field. But he needed help.
He needed Rizzo.

747
00:51:17,618 --> 00:51:21,703
Black kid with an Italian name.
With him on our side, we had a chance.

748
00:51:22,621 --> 00:51:25,622
Look, white boy, I don't know
what you play in the streets.

749
00:51:25,788 --> 00:51:28,040
I don't care. But in here,
the guards call the play...

750
00:51:28,207 --> 00:51:29,831
...and the play calls for
them to win the game.

751
00:51:29,915 --> 00:51:30,666
Why?

752
00:51:30,999 --> 00:51:31,999
Look man...

753
00:51:32,500 --> 00:51:33,999
...guards stay clear of me, all right?

754
00:51:34,166 --> 00:51:35,666
They stay back and let me do my time.

755
00:51:36,000 --> 00:51:37,835
If I play that game and I
put a hurt on one of them...

756
00:51:38,002 --> 00:51:39,628
...they just might change my cushion.

757
00:51:39,836 --> 00:51:43,003
I'm not saying we gotta win.
I just don't want to take a beating.

758
00:51:43,545 --> 00:51:44,504
You do every day.

759
00:51:45,213 --> 00:51:48,505
-Why is Saturday special?
-'Cause on Saturday, we can hit back.

760
00:51:51,673 --> 00:51:54,715
They don't fuck with you like they do us,
but they fuck with you another way!

761
00:51:54,883 --> 00:51:56,133
You're just an animal to them.

762
00:51:57,300 --> 00:51:59,967
-I don't give a fuck!
-Yeah, you do.

763
00:52:00,344 --> 00:52:02,844
And beating them on Saturday
is not gonna change a thing.

764
00:52:03,721 --> 00:52:04,887
Then why, white boy, why?

765
00:52:05,055 --> 00:52:09,430
To make them feel what we feel
...just for a couple of hours.

766
00:52:11,639 --> 00:52:13,432
Now, don't try anything funny, Sambo.

767
00:52:13,641 --> 00:52:15,767
Nobody will get hurt.
You know what I'm saying?

768
00:52:16,184 --> 00:52:17,101
I call heads.

769
00:52:20,226 --> 00:52:22,228
He called heads.
It is a head.

770
00:52:24,185 --> 00:52:25,104
Let's go.

771
00:52:35,357 --> 00:52:38,693
You're gonna die, mother fucker!
You're gonna fucking die!

772
00:52:49,405 --> 00:52:51,405
None of you motherfuckers can cover me!

773
00:52:51,739 --> 00:52:55,074
We got ourselves a game!
I'm feeling good today.

774
00:52:55,574 --> 00:52:56,740
This shit feels good.

775
00:53:03,785 --> 00:53:04,744
Fuck!

776
00:53:11,162 --> 00:53:13,164
Get the fuck off me!

777
00:53:24,460 --> 00:53:27,252
Yeah, keep smiling, you little piss ant.

778
00:53:30,254 --> 00:53:32,922
For 90 minutes, we took
the game out of the prison...

779
00:53:33,548 --> 00:53:35,464
...moved it miles beyond
the locked gates...

780
00:53:35,631 --> 00:53:37,757
...and the sloping hills of
the surrounding countryside...

781
00:53:38,383 --> 00:53:41,174
...and brought it back down to the streets
of the neighborhoods we'd come from.

782
00:53:42,425 --> 00:53:45,260
For those 90 minutes,
we were once again free!

783
00:54:04,100 --> 00:54:05,601
Rizzo! Rizzo!

784
00:54:17,522 --> 00:54:21,315
Rizzo...Rizzo.

785
00:54:23,024 --> 00:54:26,192
Hey, Nokes.
Good game.

786
00:54:29,111 --> 00:54:32,445
For once, we had a victory.
But it didn't last.

787
00:54:33,112 --> 00:54:37,447
It couldn't last...
and all I wanted to do was die.

788
00:54:38,531 --> 00:54:42,531
I was not alone in the hole. I knew my
friends were down in the depths with me.

789
00:54:43,074 --> 00:54:47,368
Each in his own cell, each in his own
pain...suffering his own demons.

790
00:54:47,993 --> 00:54:49,119
Rizzo was there, too.

791
00:54:52,161 --> 00:54:53,827
I had lost any sense of time.

792
00:55:34,677 --> 00:55:35,845
I thought you'd never wake up.

793
00:55:37,179 --> 00:55:38,513
I thought I'd never want to.

794
00:55:38,887 --> 00:55:42,055
John and Tommy, they're
on the other side there.

795
00:55:43,598 --> 00:55:47,267
How are they?
They're alive.

796
00:55:49,059 --> 00:55:50,060
Who isn't?

797
00:55:52,018 --> 00:55:52,976
Rizzo.

798
00:55:55,686 --> 00:55:56,853
They killed him?

799
00:55:58,853 --> 00:56:03,064
They took turns beating him until
there was nothing of that kid to beat.

800
00:56:07,982 --> 00:56:09,400
Rizzo was dead because of us.

801
00:56:10,816 --> 00:56:12,817
We made him think that going
up against the guards...

802
00:56:12,900 --> 00:56:14,318
...in a meaningless football game...

803
00:56:14,485 --> 00:56:18,069
...had some value...that it would
give us a reason to go on.

804
00:56:19,237 --> 00:56:20,947
Once again, we were wrong.

805
00:56:24,114 --> 00:56:25,448
Did they give you
your release date yet?

806
00:56:25,614 --> 00:56:26,948
Nokes had a letter from the warden.

807
00:56:27,782 --> 00:56:29,659
Waved it in front of me,
then tore it up....

808
00:56:30,825 --> 00:56:31,659
When do you figure?

809
00:56:33,450 --> 00:56:35,660
End of spring, early
summer or something.

810
00:56:36,743 --> 00:56:38,285
I wish we were coming with you.

811
00:56:39,327 --> 00:56:41,663
It would've been nice for all
of us to walk out together.

812
00:56:42,955 --> 00:56:46,289
No use thinking about that. We're
gonna do a full year, not an hour less.

813
00:56:48,332 --> 00:56:51,667
When I get out, I could get Father
Bobby to make a couple of phone calls.

814
00:56:51,875 --> 00:56:53,292
Shave a month or two off.

815
00:56:53,459 --> 00:56:56,126
-There's nothing to talk about!
-There's a lot to talk about.

816
00:56:56,625 --> 00:56:59,545
Maybe, if people knew what was going
on in here, they'd make a move.

817
00:57:00,129 --> 00:57:01,796
I don't want anybody to know.

818
00:57:02,587 --> 00:57:06,297
Not Father Bobby, King Benny,
Fat Mancho...

819
00:57:06,464 --> 00:57:08,798
...not my mother. Nobody.

820
00:57:10,423 --> 00:57:11,966
I don't either.

821
00:57:12,049 --> 00:57:14,299
I mean, I wouldn't know what
to say to anyone who did know.

822
00:57:15,007 --> 00:57:17,678
I can't think of anybody
who needs to hear about it.

823
00:57:18,845 --> 00:57:21,387
Either they won't believe it,
or they won't give a shit.

824
00:57:22,345 --> 00:57:24,639
Yeah, I don't even think we should
talk about it once it's over.

825
00:57:26,972 --> 00:57:30,973
We got no choice but to live with it.
And talking makes living it harder.

826
00:57:32,349 --> 00:57:34,517
So, we might as well
not even talk about it.

827
00:57:35,516 --> 00:57:36,851
The truth stays with us.

828
00:57:40,019 --> 00:57:41,853
I want to be able to sleep one night...

829
00:57:43,394 --> 00:57:46,980
...and not have to worry who's coming
in my room, what's gonna happen to me.

830
00:57:50,730 --> 00:57:54,690
If I can get that, then I'll be happy.

831
00:57:57,360 --> 00:58:00,153
Someday, John, I promise.

832
00:58:16,826 --> 00:58:20,325
I was in my last hours as an inmate
at the Wilkinson Home for boys.

833
00:58:21,161 --> 00:58:23,077
I was given four copies
of my release form.

834
00:58:23,453 --> 00:58:25,745
The final reminder of my
time at Wilkinson.

835
00:58:28,204 --> 00:58:29,788
I never heard the key
turn in the lock...

836
00:58:30,371 --> 00:58:32,456
...and I never heard
the snap of the bolt.

837
00:58:33,957 --> 00:58:35,291
You should be asleep.

838
00:58:36,541 --> 00:58:40,584
I just wanted to say goodbye.
We all do.

839
00:58:43,586 --> 00:58:45,586
I told him. I told him right
to his face. I said,

840
00:58:45,753 --> 00:58:47,587
I don't care if you're paying me
overtime or not.

841
00:58:47,670 --> 00:58:49,212
I'm not working those kind of hours.

842
00:58:49,421 --> 00:58:50,754
Yeah, did you put in for it?

843
00:58:51,254 --> 00:58:52,214
I put in for it!

844
00:58:52,256 --> 00:58:53,964
Because I put in for it.
They don't give it to me.

845
00:58:54,590 --> 00:58:57,799
I come in early for three days.
Do they give me overtime? No!

846
00:58:58,966 --> 00:59:00,926
A part of all of us was
left there that night.

847
00:59:01,968 --> 00:59:04,302
That night will never be
removed from my mind.

848
00:59:04,886 --> 00:59:09,429
The night of June 1, 1968--
the Summer of Love.

849
00:59:11,096 --> 00:59:13,097
My last night at the
Wilkinson Home for boys.

850
00:59:59,866 --> 01:00:02,532
At 8:25 p.m. two men
walked through the doors.

851
01:00:03,532 --> 01:00:06,618
The bartender knew their faces as most
of the neighborhood knew their names.

852
01:00:07,036 --> 01:00:09,661
They were two of the founding
members of the West Side Boys.

853
01:00:09,745 --> 01:00:11,245
They were also its deadliest.

854
01:00:13,329 --> 01:00:16,330
The blond-haired man had been in and out
of jail since he was a teenager.

855
01:00:16,914 --> 01:00:18,997
He robbed and killed
at will or on command.

856
01:00:19,831 --> 01:00:22,499
He was presently a suspect in
four unsolved homicides.

857
01:00:23,082 --> 01:00:26,669
He was an alcoholic and a cocaine abuser
with a fast temper and a faster trigger.

858
01:00:27,127 --> 01:00:29,961
He once shot a mechanic dead for
moving ahead of him in a movie line.

859
01:00:32,253 --> 01:00:34,254
The dark-haired man was equally deadly...

860
01:00:34,296 --> 01:00:36,588
...and had committed his
first murder at the age of 17.

861
01:00:37,463 --> 01:00:41,299
In return, he was paid $50.
He drank, and he did drugs...

862
01:00:41,464 --> 01:00:44,591
...and he had a wife he never saw,
living somewhere in Queens.

863
01:00:47,300 --> 01:00:50,719
He's making a noble attempt
to really change things.

864
01:00:50,803 --> 01:00:54,469
-The Republicans will take the House.
-Well, we got a lot of work to do.

865
01:00:54,594 --> 01:00:56,262
It's gonna take more
than 4 years to get....

866
01:00:56,429 --> 01:00:57,638
They'll take it at
the mid-term elections.

867
01:00:58,138 --> 01:01:00,972
He's got the charisma.
He's gonna do it.

868
01:01:01,182 --> 01:01:03,850
He's our man. Reagan's
the man who's gonna do it.

869
01:01:05,475 --> 01:01:07,684
Hey, Jerry...
What are they talking about?

870
01:01:08,102 --> 01:01:10,101
They're talking about Reagan's speech.

871
01:01:13,102 --> 01:01:15,604
Order those two men some
drinks and put it on my tab.

872
01:01:17,521 --> 01:01:20,355
You tell them that Republicans
are not welcome in Hell's Kitchen...

873
01:01:20,522 --> 01:01:24,023
...and either a political conversion or
a change of conversation is in order.

874
01:01:24,440 --> 01:01:25,441
Sure thing.

875
01:01:32,484 --> 01:01:35,403
The gentlemen there would like to
buy you a drink on one condition.

876
01:01:35,694 --> 01:01:39,404
You know the rules:
no religion, no politics.

877
01:01:40,028 --> 01:01:41,155
You get my meaning?

878
01:01:59,037 --> 01:02:01,330
Order something for me.
I gotta go to the bathroom.

879
01:02:32,174 --> 01:02:33,300
Can I help you with something, chief?

880
01:02:35,176 --> 01:02:39,554
Not right now.
Enjoy the rest of your meal.

881
01:03:25,613 --> 01:03:29,821
I ordered brisket on a roll,
with fries and...

882
01:03:31,239 --> 01:03:33,990
...two baskets of soda bread.
I know how you like that shit.

883
01:03:35,118 --> 01:03:36,118
Is that okay by you?

884
01:03:38,492 --> 01:03:41,577
Take a look at the guy at the table.
Take a good look.

885
01:03:53,417 --> 01:03:54,499
Motherfucker.

886
01:04:21,010 --> 01:04:22,593
That's him.

887
01:04:22,885 --> 01:04:24,302
Are you fucking kidding me?

888
01:04:27,845 --> 01:04:28,553
Bingo!

889
01:04:54,273 --> 01:04:55,397
This is amazing.

890
01:04:55,565 --> 01:04:58,233
Hello...it's been a long time!

891
01:04:59,983 --> 01:05:01,067
Who the fuck are you guys?

892
01:05:05,443 --> 01:05:07,027
Who the fuck asked you to sit down?

893
01:05:07,527 --> 01:05:10,613
I thought you'd be happy to see us.
I guess I was wrong.

894
01:05:12,447 --> 01:05:14,864
You know, I thought
you'd do a lot better.

895
01:05:15,532 --> 01:05:17,741
You know, with all that training...
all that time you put in...

896
01:05:18,366 --> 01:05:20,407
...just to end up watching
someone else's money.

897
01:05:20,742 --> 01:05:22,034
That seems like a waste.

898
01:05:22,242 --> 01:05:24,200
I'm asking you now for the last
time, what the fuck do you want?

899
01:05:24,408 --> 01:05:26,117
Why don't you take your time?
It'll come to you.

900
01:05:31,913 --> 01:05:33,706
I can see how he might forget us.

901
01:05:34,372 --> 01:05:37,289
You know, we were just something for
you and your friends to play with.

902
01:05:37,456 --> 01:05:39,582
It's a little harder for us to forget.

903
01:05:39,957 --> 01:05:42,209
You gave us so much more to remember.

904
01:05:45,583 --> 01:05:46,960
You can't quite place us,
can you, chief?

905
01:05:47,710 --> 01:05:51,712
Let me help you out. You're looking
at John Reilly and Tommy Marcano.

906
01:06:03,175 --> 01:06:04,091
Yeah, that's right.

907
01:06:10,885 --> 01:06:12,221
That was a long time ago.

908
01:06:15,762 --> 01:06:16,514
So how you been?

909
01:06:17,514 --> 01:06:19,014
Yeah, we ain't kids now.

910
01:06:20,306 --> 01:06:21,640
So, what do you want?

911
01:06:22,473 --> 01:06:25,809
What I've always wanted
is to watch you die!

912
01:06:31,854 --> 01:06:32,895
You ordered the meat loaf.

913
01:06:34,521 --> 01:06:37,522
The brisket's really good here,
only you'll never know it.

914
01:06:38,814 --> 01:06:39,646
You fucked up.

915
01:06:53,445 --> 01:06:57,779
Yeah, you were scared little pricks,
both of you.

916
01:06:59,321 --> 01:07:03,991
All of you...scared shitless.
But l...

917
01:07:05,909 --> 01:07:09,367
...l tried to make you tough.
I tried to make you hard.

918
01:07:09,408 --> 01:07:13,036
I had you all wrong then, Nokes.
All this time I thought you just liked...

919
01:07:13,202 --> 01:07:14,703
...fucking and beating up little boys.

920
01:07:14,911 --> 01:07:17,162
You two motherfuckers
are gonna burn in hell!

921
01:07:17,745 --> 01:07:19,079
You're gonna burn in hell.

922
01:07:19,247 --> 01:07:20,203
Yeah, after you.

923
01:07:25,999 --> 01:07:27,167
Did that hurt, Nokes?

924
01:08:04,682 --> 01:08:08,933
Jerry, sorry, should've made
those brisket sandwiches to go.

925
01:08:21,521 --> 01:08:22,855
John Reilly, how do you plead?

926
01:08:23,230 --> 01:08:24,397
Not guilty, Your Honor.

927
01:08:25,355 --> 01:08:26,232
Thomas Marcano?

928
01:08:27,731 --> 01:08:28,900
Not guilty, Your Honor.

929
01:08:29,439 --> 01:08:33,151
John Reilly and Thomas Marcano,
you are hereby held without bail.

930
01:08:34,358 --> 01:08:37,778
In all the years since Wilkinson's, we
had never once spoken to each other...

931
01:08:37,943 --> 01:08:41,279
...about what happened there.
We remained caring friends...

932
01:08:41,446 --> 01:08:43,446
...but the relationship
had been altered.

933
01:08:44,614 --> 01:08:48,783
We drifted together, always wondering
if that moment would arrive...

934
01:08:49,239 --> 01:08:50,990
...that would force us to
deal with the past.

935
01:09:04,497 --> 01:09:07,830
One down, Shakes, one down.

936
01:09:09,831 --> 01:09:10,663
One what?

937
01:09:12,916 --> 01:09:16,250
One Sean Nokes.

938
01:09:17,418 --> 01:09:18,293
Nokes?

939
01:09:26,587 --> 01:09:27,837
At the time of Nokes' shooting,

940
01:09:27,879 --> 01:09:30,838
Michael was working as an
Assistant New York District Attorney.

941
01:09:31,632 --> 01:09:34,384
I got a call that he wanted to meet me
on 45th Street in Queens.

942
01:09:35,217 --> 01:09:36,175
Then, he hung up.

943
01:09:40,718 --> 01:09:42,428
-So, what did they say?
-What?

944
01:09:42,678 --> 01:09:43,928
John and Tommy, what'd they say?

945
01:09:44,096 --> 01:09:45,429
It's a little cloak and
dagger, isn't it, Mike?

946
01:09:46,346 --> 01:09:48,347
Nokes?
Did they talk about him?

947
01:09:50,263 --> 01:09:51,598
-John did.
-Yeah?

948
01:09:52,473 --> 01:09:53,473
What did he say?

949
01:09:54,307 --> 01:09:56,934
He said, "One down, Shakes.
One down."

950
01:10:00,476 --> 01:10:02,477
I hear they hired Danny Snyder
as the lawyer, is that right?

951
01:10:02,645 --> 01:10:05,144
It's temporary. King Benny's
gonna move in one of his lawyers.

952
01:10:05,395 --> 01:10:08,062
Don't let him do that.
Snyder's perfect.

953
01:10:08,313 --> 01:10:10,689
-Perfect? The guy's a fall down drunk!
-Then he is perfect.

954
01:10:11,190 --> 01:10:12,314
Perfect for what?

955
01:10:16,358 --> 01:10:18,192
Are you covering this
story for your newspaper?

